Hard Ore Formed By Oxidation Of Carbonate Of Iron Formation To Soft Ore During A Period Of Mid-Proterozoic Weathering And Metamorphism During The Penokean Orogeny Which Caused The Soft Ore To Recrystallize To Hard Ore.
